Lateral region of podosoma:
Genal tooth broad, subrectangular, with dens ventrodistally, with longitudinal ridge ventrolaterally (
Fig. 2A, B
). Tutorium broadly rectangular about 121 µm long, of which cusp about 63 µm long, distal margin with 4–6 dens. Custodium about 26 µm long (
Fig. 2B
). Porose area Al about 7 µm in diameter.
